# AWS Configuration

This project uses a **dedicated AWS account**, separate from the default credentials.

| Setting        | Value                |
|----------------|----------------------|
| AWS Account ID | `572885593026`       |
| IAM User       | `hoa-admin`          |
| Region         | `us-west-2`          |
| CLI Profile    | `hoa`                |

## Required: Always Specify the Profile

**Never run bare `aws` commands.** Without the profile flag, commands hit the wrong account (`596430611773`, Stories of You).

Every AWS CLI invocation must use one of:

```powershell
# Option A: flag on every command
aws s3 ls --profile hoa --region us-west-2

# Option B: set env vars at the start of a terminal session
$env:AWS_PROFILE = "hoa"
$env:AWS_DEFAULT_REGION = "us-west-2"
```

When writing scripts, IaC (CDK/CloudFormation/Terraform), or SDK code, configure the profile/region explicitly rather than relying on defaults.

## Quick Verification

```powershell
aws sts get-caller-identity --profile hoa
# Expected: Account 572885593026, Arn ...hoa-admin
```
